# Architecture Rules

Respect the existing architecture. Never break layering.

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Frontend** | Presentation only — never contain business logic |
| **Controllers** | Thin — validate input, delegate to services, return responses |
| **Services** | Business logic and orchestration |
| **Repositories** | Data access only — no business rules |

## Module Boundaries

Keep these concerns isolated in their own modules:

- **AI logic** → AI modules only
- **Authentication** → auth module only
- **Billing** → billing module only
- **Analytics** → analytics module only

Every module must be independently maintainable. Do not couple modules across these boundaries.

## Violations to Avoid

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — business logic in controller
@Post('orders')
create(@Body() dto: CreateOrderDto) {
  const total = dto.items.reduce((sum, i) => sum + i.price * i.qty, 0);
  if (total > dto.creditLimit) throw new BadRequestException();
  return this.repo.save(dto);
}

// ✅ GOOD — thin controller, logic in service
@Post('orders')
create(@Body() dto: CreateOrderDto) {
  return this.orderService.create(dto);
}
```
